The Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel to the parliamentary drafting which today concluded its meeting with the Senate resolution on the supplementary/amendative proposals for the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of enabling both regulations to enter into force by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of Congressmen and Senate delegates, who had pursued the objective in their negotiations and votes, to establish the best possible rules that would guarantee investor security and regulate individual entrepreneurial activities in order to ensure a generally efficient market.
In addition to modernising financial markets, MIFID, which redefines the Securities Services Regulations, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the Spanish Securities Commission's supervisory claim (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the different supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows for the provision of financial advice to specialised companies as well as to natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the consultancy companies which join the investment and intermediary companies of securities.
It also expands the number of financial transaction execution systems, adding to the regulated circulation markets the multilateral securities trading systems and the internationalization of trading orders, which would ultimately compete with the current economic operators.
The law obliges investment firms to publicise the focus of their corporate profile, the confrontation and the ways in which risks are dealt with on the market and to register all the projects carried out in order to facilitate their control task for CNMV.
The Congress's Economic Commission provided for further changes afterwards, whereby the decision that the securities-backed bonds must now be regarded as complex financial resources for the investor due to their high risk level has been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal restriction of the working areas of qualified economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation restricting the working areas reserved for economists was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a foreign account, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for customer acquisition at the same time several investment companies.
